description: Lighthouse loop is a 4.4 mile trail located in discovery park near Seattle, WA. It is considered an easy route and generally takes just under 2 hours to complete. The trail is very popular for birding, hiking and trail running. Dogs are welcome but must be kept on a leash.

Lighthouse point via Bowman Bay is a 2.4 mile trail near Oak Harbor, WA. it is generally considered to be an easy route and takes about an hour and a half to complete. Dogs are welcome but must be kept on a leash.

Twin falls trail a 2.5 mile trail located near North Bend, WA. It is generally considered to be moderately difficuklt and takes about 2 hours to complete. Theres is a great view of the waterfalls at the summit during the spring. Dogs are welcome but must be kept on a leash.
